# Cursor AI Rules for TeamBalance Project

## Environment & Commands
- Use Windows PowerShell commands only (not bash/linux commands)
- Use `pnpm` as the package manager
- Use `npx` for running packages when needed
- Always use PowerShell syntax for file operations

## Server Management
- DO NOT start/stop development servers (`pnpm dev`, `npm start`, etc.)
- DO NOT run background processes
- User will handle server execution manually
- Focus on code changes and file operations only

## Build Requirements
- After all changes are completed, ALWAYS run `pnpm build`
- If build errors occur, resolve them immediately
- Ensure production build succeeds before completing tasks

## Project Structure
- This is a Next.js 15 project with TypeScript
- Uses Tailwind CSS v4 with F1 Racing theme
- NextAuth.js v5 for authentication
- Prisma with PostgreSQL (NeonDB)
- shadcn/ui components

## Code Style & Preferences
- F1 Racing theme with dark colors (black, red, yellow, silver)
- Use Korean language for user-facing text
- Professional racing terminology in UI
- Font: Rajdhani (body), Orbitron (titles)
- Prefer modern React patterns (Server Components, Server Actions)

## File Operations
- Always use relative paths from project root
- Check file existence before editing
- Use proper TypeScript types
- Follow Next.js App Router conventions

## Database & Auth
- Prisma schema uses enum types for levels/roles
- NextAuth configured with Kakao OAuth
- Use Node.js runtime for API routes (not Edge)
- Session-based authentication

## Responses
- Always respond in Korean language
- Be concise but thorough
- Provide clear explanations for changes
- Use appropriate technical terminology

